  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Stand-alone apps are apps that don’t rely on any 3rd-party system-wide dependencies being installed",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "on the user’s system. For example, if you build an executable that uses Gtk3, it isn’t stand-alone",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and it won’t run on any system without Gtk3 installed. However, fear no more! Swift Bundler has a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "solution.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "The-Swift-Bundler-solution",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "The Swift Bundler solution",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When building your app for macOS, try using the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--experimental-stand-alone",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag to automatically",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "relocate all 3rd-party system-wide dynamic library dependencies of your app into the app bundle.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This works quite effectively for Gtk, however, you will run into issues when trying to create a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "universal binary. In particular, universal builds will only be truly universal if the system-wide",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "dependencies of your app were built as universal binaries when you installed them (not the case if",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "you used Homebrew). If you are building on Intel, the built app might be able to run on Apple Silicon",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "because of Rosetta (untested), however it definitely won’t work the other way around.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
